<item>
            <title>[LU-12190] how to apply patchs to rpm based package</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12190</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have installed lustre 2.10.5 on CentOS 7.5&#65292;recently we met some problems already resolved in new release&#65292;so we want to update our lustre to 2.10.7.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I found some bug report for 2.10.7 and the patch released&#65292;So, I want to patch it but I do not know how to.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there any docs described how to apply patchs to a rpm based install of lustre ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="55422">LU-12190</key>
            <summary>how to apply patchs to rpm based package</summary>
                <type id="9" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/issuetypes/undefined.png">Question/Request</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg">Minor</priority>
